I make these because it's fun and people like them, it's also nice to practice modeling since I'll need it for the games I'm working on.
Heather had a few inspirations but there were mainly two big ones. The first one is that I really like making puns and I really like computer science, so Heather was a way to make a whole lot of compsci puns, even her name is a play on the term header file. The second was Lynn, DV really knew what he was doing when he made her. She has an easy to draw design, a strong personality, and is very easy to like. And you can tell how well it worked from all of the drawings people make of her and all the fun people have with writing short greentexts about her. I wanted to make a thread waifur of my own, so I used those bullet points as a template for my OC.
Her design took a little bit longer to nail down. One of the Ideas for her was that she was a mascot for an energy drink, with a bunny girl that hated energy drinks forced to wear the costume for her job, but I didn’t really like that one. There was a robot doe one, I think I posted that sketch before. But then I was messing around and made this drawing that was a merger of the two designs. And then about 2 weeks after I finished her design I made Icce on an aggie and she got way more popular then Heather. Moral of the story, draw what you want and don’t worry if it’ll get popular. As for why she’s a bunny, I like bunnies.
I continue doing it because it’s fun to do. I like modeling, I like drawing, and I like the responses you guys give.
